cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "IntP -- Interference Profiler: Multi-Variant Comparison"
abstract: >
  Seven implementation variants of IntP, an interference profiler that collects
  7 metrics from the Linux kernel. Developed as part of a Master's dissertation
  on kernel instrumentation for interference profiling, comparing the original
  SystemTap-based IntP and an RCU-safe stap+helper hybrid against modern
  instrumentation approaches (procfs polling, bpftrace, eBPF/CO-RE) to
  evaluate portability, safety, and measurement fidelity tradeoffs.
authors:
